<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1A387EFF78FC13FDE3FBFA" pageId="587" pageNumber="588" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFF78FC13FDE3FBFA" blockId="587.[136,778,989,2070]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFF78FC13FEFBFC36" bold="true" box="[189,318,989,1015]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFF09FBCEFF35FBD8" box="[204,240,1024,1049]" italics="true" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">uni</emphasis>
(=one) and 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFEBAFC31FE78FBD8" box="[383,445,1023,1049]" italics="true" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">pedat</emphasis>
(=having feet), and refers to the presence of only one pair of legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1A387EFF78FB8DFBE5FA12" pageId="587" pageNumber="588" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFF78FB8DFDD3FA34" blockId="587.[136,778,989,2070]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFF78FB8DFE7CFB9C" bold="true" box="[189,441,1091,1117]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFDD5FB8DFD47FB9F" box="[528,642,1091,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395A</figureCitation>
) caterpillarlike, strongly curved ventrally, surface densely covered with fine setules: consistingof unsegmented prosome and small free urosome. Body length 2.45 mm; greatest width of prosome 545 μm across posterior part. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFF55FB23FECDFAC9" box="[144,264,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395B</figureCitation>
) as long as wide, defined from metasomal region by weak constriction. Rostral region produced anteriorly. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFE6EFAFFFDDBFA8D" box="[427,542,1329,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395C</figureCitation>
) short, 160 μmlong, consistingof genitalsomiteand 2 abdominal somites. Genital somite bearing copulatory pore on ventral surface. Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFEE1FA59FE5DFA73" box="[292,408,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395C</figureCitation>
) fused with anal somite, as long as wide, ornamented with setules mainly distally; armed with 1 small, bifurcate seta distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFF78FA30FD01F88B" blockId="587.[136,778,989,2070]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
Rostrum as prominence on frontal margin of cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFEFEF9D1FE06F9FB" box="[315,451,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395B</figureCitation>
). Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFDB9F9D1FCC7F9FB" box="[636,770,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395D</figureCitation>
) attenuated, about 120 μm long, unsegmented with several partial suture line along posterior side; densely covered with setules, setae small, similar in form to setules. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFF3AF969FEBCF903" box="[255,377,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395E</figureCitation>
) slender, 3-segmented; coxa and basis unarmed; unsegmented endopod 2.9 times longer than wide (58×20 μm); armed with 4 small setae (1 on proximal inner margin, 1 subdistal, and 2 distal) plus very small terminal claw, about 20% length of endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFF78F89CFBB9FAC6" blockId="587.[136,778,989,2070]" lastBlockId="587.[810,1452,989,1696]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFEE2F89CFE5CF8AD" box="[295,409,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395F</figureCitation>
) shortand broad, withrounded, setulose posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFDBFF8BAFCC7F84F" box="[634,770,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395G</figureCitation>
) consisting of coxa with extended gnathobase bearing pectinate medial margin and markedly convex distal margin, and biramous palp armed with 4 setae on exopod and 1 seta on basis; endopod only partially demarcated from basis, with 2 setae on first segment and 3 setae on second. Maxillule (( 
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFBC9FC31FBBBFBDB" box="[1036,1150,1023,1050]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395H</figureCitation>
) consisting of precoxa and unsegmented, lobate palp; with 3 setaeon medial margin of precoxal arthrite and 6 setae on palp; all setae broad and pinnate. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFC32FBABFBA6FB41" box="[1015,1123,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395I</figureCitation>
) 2-segmented; first segment with 2 setae; second segment subdivided by partial suture line, armed with 2 smaller medial and 2 larger distal setae; all setae pinnate. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFBB3FB05FB24FB27" box="[1142,1249,1227,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395J</figureCitation>
) lobate, bearing 5 subequal, naked setae distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFC9AFADEFB1BFA70" blockId="587.[810,1452,989,1696]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
Leg 1 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED1A387EFC78FAC1FBFDFAEB" box="[957,1080,1295,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 395" captionStartId="588.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[214,1332,218,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@588.[214,1373,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="588" captionText="FIGURE 395. Procampodelphys unipedatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, labrum; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–I, K, 0.02 mm; J, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592106/files/figure.png" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Fig. 395K</figureCitation>
) densely covered with setules, obscurely 2-segmented; first segment (protopod) with outerdistalseta; secondsegment bilobed, with 2 setae distally on longer outer lobe (exopod) and 1 seta distally on shorter inner lobe. Legs 2–5 absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFC9AFA74FBE5FA12" blockId="587.[810,1452,989,1696]" box="[863,1056,1465,1492]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFC9AFA74FC59FA15" bold="true" box="[863,924,1466,1492]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1A387EFC9AFA12FC69F961" pageId="587" pageNumber="588" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1A387EFC9AFA12FC69F961" blockId="587.[810,1452,989,1696]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1A387EFC9AFA12FC09FA37" bold="true" box="[863,972,1500,1526]" pageId="587" pageNumber="588">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is distinguishable from its four congeneric species by its 2-segmented maxilla (3-segmented in congeners), by the possession of 5 setae on the maxilliped (6 or 7 setae in congeners), and by the absence of legs 2–4 (legs 2 and 3, at least, are present in congeners).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
